fore-published photographs, From Stalin to Mao draws on a wealth of Albanian, Russian, German, British, Italian, Czech, and American archival sources, in addition to fiction, interviews, and memoirs. Mëhilli’s fresh perspective on the Soviet-Chinese battle for the soul of revolution in the global Cold War also illuminates the paradoxes of state planning in the twentieth century.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 26. Mrz 2024) 0aCity planningzAlbaniaxHistoryy20th century. 0aSocialism and culturezAlbania. 4aHistory. 4aPolitical Science & Political History. 4aSoviet & East European History.  aStalinism, Maoism, Communism, Socialism, political alliances, history of communist Albania, transnational exchange.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertCornell University Press Complete eBook-Package 2017z978311066587140uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/9781501709593?locatt=mode:legacy40uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781501709593423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781501709593/original  a978-3-11-066587-1  Cornell University Press Complete eBook-Package 2017b2017  aGBV-deGruyter-alles